&gt; &gt; &gt;&gt;&gt; What Frank is referring to is more properly termed a
&gt; &quot;Pseudo-Skeptic&quot;.
&gt; &gt; &gt;&gt;&gt; Indeed Skepticism is a vital part of scientific investigations, but
&gt; it&#39;s
&gt; &gt; &gt;&gt;&gt; Skepticism based on consideration of the facts and expressing a
&gt; caution or
&gt; &gt; &gt;&gt;&gt; difference of opinion is what is useful in the Scientific community.
&gt; A
&gt; &gt; &gt;&gt;&gt; pseudo Skeptic is characterized by a person who clearly does not know
&gt; the
&gt; &gt; &gt;&gt;&gt; subject area other than through what may be termed &quot;common knowledge&quot;
&gt; or, at
&gt; &gt; &gt;&gt;&gt; best, a brief overview of the literature. A Pseudo skeptic&#39;s
&gt; &quot;opinions&quot;
&gt; &gt; &gt;&gt;&gt; are based primarily on an emotional attitude towards the subject
&gt; matter
&gt; &gt; &gt;&gt;&gt; rather than what few &quot;facts&quot; he knows. Its a psychological defense he
&gt; uses
&gt; &gt; &gt;&gt;&gt; to shore up his status, the validity of his work, and to cope with
&gt; things
&gt; &gt; &gt;&gt;&gt; that frighten him.
&gt; &gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt;&gt;&gt; A real Skeptic is a friend with a difference of opinion based on a
&gt; &gt; &gt;&gt;&gt; genuine desire to help and sufficient data on the subject at hand to
&gt; know
&gt; &gt; &gt;&gt;&gt; what he/she is talking about. We, as Scientists must always have a
&gt; health
&gt; &gt; &gt;&gt;&gt; dose of real Skepticism. Otherwise we risk being the exact inverse of
&gt; the
&gt; &gt; &gt;&gt;&gt; Pseudo skeptic---the &quot;FLAKE&quot;. The Flake is the type who will believe
&gt; &gt; &gt;&gt;&gt; anything. Just as the Pseudo Skeptic has a need to reject things on
&gt; &gt; &gt;&gt;&gt; emotional grounds, the Flake has a need to accept EVERYTHING on
&gt; emotional
&gt; &gt; &gt;&gt;&gt; grounds. Any shadow, sound, or corner of the eye flash just HAS to be
&gt; a
&gt; &gt; &gt;&gt;&gt; ghost or spirit. ----or whatever. I think you know the type, and
&gt; these
&gt; &gt; &gt;&gt;&gt; &quot;flakes&quot; are what Pseudo skeptics accuse us who are serious about
&gt; paranormal
&gt; &gt; &gt;&gt;&gt; studies of being. Perhaps its one of the reasons they get us so
&gt; angry.
&gt; &gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;
